President Muhammadu Buhari has met with the released students of Government Science Secondary School in Kankara. Buhari met with the 344 students on Friday in Katsina State. Recall that the students were last week kidnapped by some gunmen said to be bandits. The students were taken to the bandits hideout in Tsafe, Zamfara State. However, the bandits had last night released the students. The students were said to have been released following the intervention of security personnel and the Miyetti Allah association.